            . I live in <placeName id="t18140216-10-crimeloc51">High Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18140216-10-crimeloc51" type="placeName" value="High Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18140216-10-crimeloc51" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18140216-10-off49 t18140216-10-crimeloc51"></join>; I am a <rs id="t18140216-10-viclabel52" type="occupation">pocket-book maker, and work-box maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18140216-10-victim129 t18140216-10-viclabel52"></join>. On the 8th of February, in consequence of information, I followed the prisoner; I overtook her about thirty yards from my shop with a Russian shaving-box upon her. This is the shaving-box; I can say it is mine. I overtook her as she was wrapping it up in a building round the corner of the street. I had seen the shaving-box in my shop not five minutes before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18140216-10-person131">
                  ANN 
                  MARTIN
               <interp inst="t18140216-10-person131" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140216-10-person131" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140216-10-person131" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My shop is next door to Mr. Batley's shop; there is a glass door to each shop; one looks into the other. On the 8th of February, I saw the prisoner open the door and go into Mr. Batley's shop. There is a small bell to the door; she opened the door cautiously; it did not ring the bell. I saw her lift her arm across the counter, and take the outside box. There were two boxes.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you see what she took - A. Yes, the shaving box; she then went out with it under her arm uncovered; I gave notice to Mr. Batley; he went after her directly.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I throw myself on the mercy of the court.</p>
               <p>GUILTY, aged 43,</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18140216-10-verdict53" type="verdictDescription">
